Privacy Policy
Blue Islands is committed to looking after your Personal Information and respecting your privacy, We will be transparent in how your data is used and only process your data responsibly and in accordance with data protection legislation.
We care about your data, this Privacy Policy provides information to assist you to understand details of how we collect and process your Personal Information.
“Personal Information” in this policy refers to any information that identifies or relates to you including your name, travel itinerary and contact details along with information collected on your use of our website or app.
We only collect information that is required to provide our services to you, improve those services and/or required by law.
1. Who we are and what are our responsibilities
This Privacy Policy applies to the Personal Information that Blue Islands’ collects and uses.
Blue Islands Ltd
Registered in Alderney, company no. 1344.
Unit 7
Martyn House
Queen Elizabeth II Street
Alderney
GY9 3TB
Blue Islands is a Channel Islands based operator, registered in Alderney. However, as a business serving customers in multiple jurisdictions, a variety of Data Protection Laws may apply to Blue Islands depending on the scenario. Given our location and network, the three most likely applicable laws are as below:
Guernsey
Data Protection (Bailiwick of Guernsey) Law, 2017
Jersey
Data Protection (Jersey) Law 2018
United Kingdom
Data Protection Act 2018
Blue Islands is a Controller under Data Protection Law and takes its data protection responsibilities seriously.. The Blue Islands Privacy Policy contains important information about how we process your Personal Information and your rights.
2. The Personal Information we collect and process about you
Blue Islands operates scheduled flights and series and ad-hoc charter flights. Seats for Blue Islands’ flights are sold through blueislands.com, our app or through a third party.
Blue Islands will collect and process Personal Information (and Special Categories of Personal Information) about you at different points in our relationship with you.
If you book a Blue Islands flight or a flight operated by Blue Islands through a third party (for example an online travel agent or holiday company), then that third party will send us Personal Information about you that we will use to provide the flight or service.
We collect and process your Personal Information for a number of purposes, details of which can be found below
2.1 Making a booking
Personal Information
Purpose and lawful basis
Bookers name, surname and contact details
Age band (Adult, Child, Youth or Infant)
Booking reference
Itinerary
Passenger names
This information is required in order for us to manage your booking and to fulfil our contract with you.
Payment card details
This information is required to complete payment for your booking, and therefore in order for us to fulfil our contract with you.
Blue Skies membership number
This information is required for us to allocate your Blue Skies Points to your account should you choose to enrol in the scheme. This is therefore required for us to perform our contract with you.
2.2 Travelling with us
Personal Information
Purpose and lawful basis
Passenger names
Seat numbers
Flight date and flight number
Origin and Destination
Special Requirements (e.g wheelchair assistance)
This information is required to comply with our legal obligation to confirm only passengers booked to travel do so and to deliver appropriate assistance to those travelling with us.
2.3 Flight Disruption
Personal Information
Purpose and lawful basis
Contact details and itinerary
This information is used to notify you of any changes to your flight and is processed to fulfil our legal obligation.
Disruption claim information including name, itinerary, contact details and bank account details
This information is used to process and assess any claims made by you as a result of flight disruption to fulfil our legal obligation.
2.4 Advance Passenger Information
Personal Information
Purpose and lawful basis
Passenger name
Nationality
Date of Birth
Gender
Travel Document (e.g. passport) details
Depending on where you are travelling with us, we may be required to transmit this information to the border control agencies of the origin or destination country. This is done in order to comply with our legal obligations.
2.5 Marketing
Personal Information
Purpose and lawful basis
Contact details
Booking history
This Personal Information is processed for our legitimate interest of communicating with you about services that we believe will be of interest to you.
Where  there  is a legal requirement for us to have your consent prior to contacting you for marketing purposes, we will only contact you if you have consented, with consent then being our legal basis for processing your data
For all Blue Islands email marketing communications, a Preference Centre allows you to view and make certain decisions and preferences regarding what you receive. The Preference Centre allows you to Unsubscribe at any time and this is clearly linked to all emails and communications for marketing purposes.
2.6 Special Categories of Personal Information
We do process the following types of Special Categories of Personal Information:
health and disability information, which you provide to us when requesting any form of passenger assistance
racial or ethnic origin (i.e. nationality), which you provide to us when completing your booking or providing Advance Passenger Information
2.7 Personal Information of your Group
If you are organising a group booking directly with Blue Islands, you must have the consent from the individual group members to provide the above Personal Information (and in some cases Special Categories of Personal Information).
2.8 Technical Information
When you interact with our website or app, we collect a range of Technical Information about how you interact with and access these platforms. Such Technical Information includes IP (Internet Protocol) Address, browser type and version.
3. When do we collect Personal Information
when you browse or visit blueislands.com;
if you submit your Personal Information on blueislands.com;
if you subscribe to a Blue Islands email;
if you enter a competition;
if you provide feedback;
if you email, write or call Blue Islands;
if you email, write or call a third party regarding a Blue Islands operated flight and this is passed to Blue Islands;
if you book a flight;
if you enrol in our frequent flyer loyalty scheme;
if you make a group booking or charter booking on a Blue Islands operated flight;
if you make a booking on a flight or charter flight operated by Blue Islands, that is booked through a third party
if you consent to take part in promotional activity for Blue Islands’ products and services.
Blue Islands will share your Personal Information with third party service providers that act on our behalf to provide services to us. Examples are companies that provide ground handling services at airports and our payment processing partner to enable you to pay for services.
Blue Islands carefully selects these partners, will only ever partner with reputable third parties and ensures that contractual provisions are in place to protect all Personal Information.
In addition to the Advanced Passenger Information, we may disclose Personal Information to customs and immigration authorities, border control agencies, law enforcement bodies and other relevant authorities when this is necessary to get you to your destination or is required by law.
We use cookies, which are text files containing small amounts of information that are downloaded to your computer or mobile device. To find out more click here: Cookie Policy
