ACTUARY DATA PRIVACY STATEMENT
If you see an undefined term in this Privacy Policy (such as “transactions” or “Actuary Platform”), it has the same definition as outlined in our Terms & Services.
When this policy mentions “Actuary,” “we,” “us,” or “our,” it refers to the Actuary company that is responsible for your information under this Privacy Policy:
You the data subject/consumer
The Data Controllers, (i.e., acquirers, merchants)
The Data processor is Actuary BV (“
Actuary BV
”) for our platform.
The Data controller Actuary BV in case you visit our general company webpage as a data subject
If you change your place or location, the Data Controller and/or Processor will be determined by your (new) place of residence or location as specified above, from the date on which your place of residence changes.
There are three general categories of information we collect. All are subject to who & what you are visiting on the Actuary website or platform.
‍
The Actuary platform is intended for our customers and only accessible via a (customer/company) login. You will be visiting our platform as a company employee and not as consumer/ data subject.
The general Actuary website is accessible to everyone and only contains general company information and basic communication functions: information on our services and contact information.
Nevertheless, in this policy we prefer to be transparent on our data use and your privacy.
We collect information from our users when they use the Actuary Platform.
Account Information.
When we receive a sign-up request directly or via Mastercard Connect for an Actuary Account, we require certain information such as your company, name, email address, etc. And the sign-up needs to be approved by the central contact person within the customer.
Authentication-Related Information.
To help create and maintain a trusted environment, we collect the usernames & passwords or other authentication related information
Communications with Actuary.
When you communicate with Actuary, we collect information about your communication, and information requests.
Cookies and Similar Technologies.
We use cookies and other similar technologies, such as web beacons and mobile identifiers. While you may disable the usage of cookies through your browser settings, we do not change our practices in response to a “Do Not Track” signal in the HTTP header from your browser or mobile application. We use these cookies for a better browsing experience. For more information on our use of these technologies, see our
cookie policy
.
Other Information.
You may otherwise choose to provide us information when you fill in a form, conduct a search, update, or add information to your Actuary Account, respond to surveys, post to community forums, participate in promotions, or use other features of the Actuary Platform.
When Customers use the Actuary Platform, we process information about the services you use and how you use them.
Usage Information.
We collect information about your interactions with the Actuary Platform, such as the pages or other content you view.
Location Information.
When you use certain features of the Actuary Platform, we may collect different types of information about your general location (e.g., IP address, zip code) or more specific location information (e.g. precise location from your mobile GPS). Most mobile devices allow you to control or disable the use of location services for applications in the device’s settings menu.
Communications with Actuary.
When you communicate with Actuary, we collect information about your communication, and information requests.
Log Data.
We automatically collect log information when you use the Actuary Platform, even if you don’t have an Actuary Account or are logged in. That information includes, among other things: details about how you’ve used the Actuary Platform and the page you’ve viewed or engaged with using the Actuary Platform.
Cookies and Similar Technologies.
We use cookies and other similar technologies, such as web beacons and mobile identifiers. While you may disable the usage of cookies through your browser settings, we do not change our practices in response to a “Do Not Track” signal in the HTTP header from your browser or mobile application. We use these cookies for a better browsing experience. For more information on our use of these technologies, see our cookie policy.
We may share your information at your direction or as described in our Terms & Services, such as when you authorize consent, access our Services via your Actuary Account or when you choose to submit your information via a contact form.
If Actuary undertakes or is involved in any merger, acquisition, reorganization, sale of assets, bankruptcy, or insolvency event, then we may sell, transfer, or share some or all our assets, including your information. In this event, we will notify you before your personal information is transferred and becomes subject to a different privacy policy.
Platform data: we store the transaction data we receive from acquirers and merchants for [1] year after the contract termination date unless the customer has requested us in writing to delete the information immediately after the contract termination date.
‍
Platform user information: user information, location information, log data, cookies, and similar technologies (like Google analytics): we store this data for [5] years after the contract termination date unless the customer requests us in writing to delete it immediately after the contract termination date.
General Actuary Website (User) information: via our website we collect, and store data provided via our Contact & information request page and process & store this data for the time needed to handle the request properly. In our webpage logs we store log data to keep the website up and running and functioning as intended. These website logs are cycled automated & periodically to provide normal services to our users & visitors. This data is stored for a maximum of [5] years, unless we receive a request to delete/adjust personal data related to a data subject immediately.
Based on the AVG there are a couple of requests that you can submit to us as a data subject.
Requests can be:
The right of access: the right to receive a copy of the personal data that is being processed.
The right to be forgotten: the right of erasing personal data
The right to rectification and addition: the right to adjust the personal data that we process on behalf of third parties.
The right of data portability: the right to have personal data transferred to another party.
The right to restriction of processing: the right to have less data being processed.
The right regarding automated decision-making and profiling: the right to a human eye when making decisions.
The right to object against data processing.
We are continuously implementing and updating administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect your information against unauthorized access, loss, destruction, or alteration. However, the Internet is not a 100% secure environment so we can’t guarantee the security of the transmission or storage of your information.
Actuary reserves the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time in accordance with this provision. If we make changes to this Privacy Policy, we will post the revised Privacy Policy on the Actuary website and update the “Last Updated” date at the top of this Privacy Policy. We will also provide you with notice of the modification by a pop-up upon visit or email at least thirty (30) days before the date they become effective. If you disagree with the revised Privacy Policy, you may cancel your subscription. If you do not cancel your subscription before the date the revised Privacy Policy becomes effective, your continued access or use will constitute acceptance of the revised Privacy Policy.
If you have any questions or suggestion about this Privacy Policy or Actuary information handling practices, you may contact us at:
Actuary BV, Data Protection Officer, Korte Hogendijk 16, 1506MA Zaandam, The Netherlands.
‍
You may also e-mail us at support@actuary.aero
